  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DSK Localised emergency response transition of essential health, WaSH, and protection services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Critical WASH Support for 16,000 Rohingya people and host communities
Improved awareness and access to GBV response and prevention services for 4000 Rohingya refugees</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to increase knowledge and awareness of Rohingya refugees on protection issues and ensure their access to GBV response and prevention services on protection issues such as human trafficking, child/early marriage, dowry, domestic violence, rape and sexual exploitation
Continued operation and maintenance of WaSH infrastructure together with hygiene promotion will minimise the continued threats posed by poor hygiene and resulting health concerns which disproportionately affect women, girls and PWD. The extremely high population density in the camps combined with poor WaSH facilities will only be made worse with the start of the monsoon season which will inevitably increase the risk of contracting COVID-19, particularly for the elderly</narrative>
  </description>
